# CLI via API only

All `tt` functionality must call the BLVD Timesheet HTTP API. The CLI is a thin client — it does not own business rules or persistence.

## Do

- Use `internal/api` (or equivalent) HTTP client for every mutation and query
- Read/write config and credentials locally only (`~/.tt/config`)
- Surface API errors to the user; do not re-implement validation the API already enforces

## Do not

- Import or call AWS SDKs (`dynamodb`, `s3`, etc.) for application data
- Embed DynamoDB PK/SK logic, entity shapes, or integrity rules in CLI code
- Add "fast path" scripts that bypass the API for writes

## Examples

```go
// ❌ BAD — direct DynamoDB in CLI
svc.PutItem(ctx, &dynamodb.PutItemInput{...})

// ✅ GOOD — API does the work
client.CreatePerson(ctx, req)
```

When the API lacks an endpoint for a workflow, add it in **time-tracker-api** first, then wire the CLI to that endpoint.
